> @brijyot set SHUUP_ENABLE_MULTIPLE_SHOPS to True in project settings.py
> But each shop must have own domain and u can't switch beetwen shops in admin.

@dansamara yes, you can change the shop in the admin. The user must be connected to more than 1 shop. To connect make sure the user is in the Shop staff member list. Then, use the search field in admin to change the shop, type the shop name and it will be visible there as an action to change it.

@FMajesty you can also `pip install shuup-stripe` and add it to your project installed apps manually. With workbench edit either base or local-settings.

Something like this for local_settings.py should do it:
```
def configure(setup):
    setup.INSTALLED_APPS = list(setup.INSTALLED_APPS) + ["shuup_stripe"]
```

